---
By: William James
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 26
    Verse: 14
Tags:
  - Apathy/Inertia
---
There is no more miserable human being than one in whom nothing is habitual
but indecision. Fully half ofthe time of such a man goes to the deciding, or
regretting of matters.
